  "texts": [
    "Diffusion models were developed by Stanford researchers in 2015 (21).",
    "They are probabilistic generative models that work by iteratively injecting Gaussian noise into the data.",
    "Then, a series of probabilistic denoising steps are applied to reverse this procedure and generate new data samples (22).",
    "Diffusion models have found applications, especially in image generation (23), synthesis (24), and image super-resolution (25).",
    "They are the architecture of popular image generation services, such as Dall-E 2, Stable Diffusion, and Midjourney."
  ],
